  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 61-year-old man is brought by his daughter to the clinic for evaluation of progressive difficulty walking over two weeks. He frequently staggers and knocks objects off the table when reaching for them. On examination, he has a wide-based gait, repeatedly misses his nose during finger–nose testing, and struggles with rapid alternating hand movements. There is no muscle weakness or sensory loss.\nWhich of the following lesions is most likely responsible for these findings?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Anterior horn of the spinal cord"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Lateral cerebellar hemisphere"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Dorsal columns of the spinal cord"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Substantia nigra pars reticulata"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Lesions in the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=G60BmS&anker=Zb07cb748c2c1920aebde647ceb16aaef\" data-learningcard-id=\"G60BmS\" data-anker=\"Zb07cb748c2c1920aebde647ceb16aaef\" data-section-id=\"Nuc-rV0\" data-sememe-id=\"l3XviB\">anterior horn</a> affect <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=G60BmS&anker=Z8ad1756cfe9f1471d86167ddbf4e78b4\" data-learningcard-id=\"G60BmS\" data-anker=\"Z8ad1756cfe9f1471d86167ddbf4e78b4\" data-section-id=\"Nuc-rV0\" data-sememe-id=\"f4bkiF\">lower motor neurons</a>, leading to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3u0SI3&anker=Z93d62f5be98d30767aafeed41bff21b0\" data-learningcard-id=\"3u0SI3\" data-anker=\"Z93d62f5be98d30767aafeed41bff21b0\" data-section-id=\"WVdPtK0\" data-sememe-id=\"PaVWkG0\">muscle weakness</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Za78e93e8d8af6655bfa6f64569ad19e2\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Za78e93e8d8af6655bfa6f64569ad19e2\" data-section-id=\"aFXQg-\" data-sememe-id=\"dwYo3r\">atrophy</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Ze95f9b2d232251637659c74f5b471b2e\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Ze95f9b2d232251637659c74f5b471b2e\" data-section-id=\"EAX8l00\" data-sememe-id=\"IhbY2t\">fasciculations</a>, and diminished reflexes. The patient's symptoms of wide-based gait, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BR0z6f&anker=Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-learningcard-id=\"BR0z6f\" data-anker=\"Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-section-id=\"J8asnm\" data-sememe-id=\"zf0rK2\">dysmetria</a>, and difficulty with rapid alternating movements indicate coordination issues, not strength deficits, and there is no <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3u0SI3&anker=Z93d62f5be98d30767aafeed41bff21b0\" data-learningcard-id=\"3u0SI3\" data-anker=\"Z93d62f5be98d30767aafeed41bff21b0\" data-section-id=\"WVdPtK0\" data-sememe-id=\"PaVWkG0\">muscle weakness</a> or sensory loss.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">lateral</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lp0wJS&anker=Zed6addcdf2d648402a0336b719cb5a1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lp0wJS\" data-anker=\"Zed6addcdf2d648402a0336b719cb5a1f\" data-section-id=\"Txc6De0\" data-sememe-id=\"CAXqN00\">cerebellar hemisphere</a>, part of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lp0wJS&anker=Z30d8cb078c72a87000b7de6b42a2bb38\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lp0wJS\" data-anker=\"Z30d8cb078c72a87000b7de6b42a2bb38\" data-section-id=\"VxcGve0\">cerebrocerebellum</a>, is crucial for planning and coordinating fine voluntary movements. Lesions here lead to limb <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BR0z6f&anker=Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-learningcard-id=\"BR0z6f\" data-anker=\"Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-section-id=\"J8asnm\" data-sememe-id=\"zf0rK2\">dysmetria</a>, seen as inaccurate targeting in tasks like the finger–nose test, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Z9ee37d95703755df723f2aede018c2ac\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Z9ee37d95703755df723f2aede018c2ac\" data-section-id=\"DAX1N00\" data-sememe-id=\"_f05K2\">dysdiadochokinesia</a>, evident in difficulties with rapid alternating movements. The output from this region, primarily via the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lp0wJS&anker=Zed57e201bc2f796bbe3d9549e09c4874\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lp0wJS\" data-anker=\"Zed57e201bc2f796bbe3d9549e09c4874\" data-section-id=\"2xcTDe0\" data-sememe-id=\"2_XTn00\">dentate nucleus</a> to the motor cortex through the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-60DnS&anker=Zd64bfb19d2d1ca43c42b4d2c203deb2f\" data-learningcard-id=\"-60DnS\" data-anker=\"Zd64bfb19d2d1ca43c42b4d2c203deb2f\" data-section-id=\"Fvcgbe0\" data-sememe-id=\"ScXybC\">thalamus</a>, refines motor <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zc281b3447500bc4fe3f96f8387f64822\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zc281b3447500bc4fe3f96f8387f64822\" data-section-id=\"vfWALk0\" data-sememe-id=\"_Ha5GN\">precision</a> and timing. This explains the patient's wide-based gait and incoordination without <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3u0SI3&anker=Z93d62f5be98d30767aafeed41bff21b0\" data-learningcard-id=\"3u0SI3\" data-anker=\"Z93d62f5be98d30767aafeed41bff21b0\" data-section-id=\"WVdPtK0\" data-sememe-id=\"PaVWkG0\">muscle weakness</a> or sensory deficits, aligning with the role of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">lateral</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lp0wJS&anker=Zed6addcdf2d648402a0336b719cb5a1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lp0wJS\" data-anker=\"Zed6addcdf2d648402a0336b719cb5a1f\" data-section-id=\"Txc6De0\" data-sememe-id=\"CAXqN00\">cerebellar hemisphere</a> in executing coordinated, goal-directed movements.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point: </b></span>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Lp0wJS&anker=Z41d8fdaf426af02446dddd77a7bdb023\" data-learningcard-id=\"Lp0wJS\" data-anker=\"Z41d8fdaf426af02446dddd77a7bdb023\" data-sememe-id=\"eacxja0\">cerebellum</a> is responsible for coordination of voluntary movements, and damage to this area can result in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BR0z6f&anker=Zf80a28124dec1e83d16823b0ca5e4295\" data-learningcard-id=\"BR0z6f\" data-anker=\"Zf80a28124dec1e83d16823b0ca5e4295\" data-section-id=\"MjcMac0\" data-sememe-id=\"of00M2\">ataxia</a>, affecting tasks such as bringing a fork to the mouth.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=G60BmS&anker=Z3bdd63076128f8729c578ddd9af9bf86\" data-learningcard-id=\"G60BmS\" data-anker=\"Z3bdd63076128f8729c578ddd9af9bf86\" data-section-id=\"SucyqV0\" data-sememe-id=\"-hXDgB\">dorsal columns</a> transmit <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Z56b78ebccefe6bf59439f506556ff19d\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Z56b78ebccefe6bf59439f506556ff19d\" data-section-id=\"FAXgl00\" data-sememe-id=\"bqaHCl\">proprioception</a>, vibration, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Z7f6708024ef1197ee905691fb886af5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Z7f6708024ef1197ee905691fb886af5a\" data-section-id=\"FAXgl00\">fine touch</a>. Lesions here cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Z111cf9ee60c2fa9979efa650c8a18cc5\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Z111cf9ee60c2fa9979efa650c8a18cc5\" data-section-id=\"CAXqN00\" data-sememe-id=\"3NbSa8\">sensory ataxia</a>, a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Zf1eba4cc32ca2ffe81b8743e760f0734\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Zf1eba4cc32ca2ffe81b8743e760f0734\" data-section-id=\"CAXqN00\">positive Romberg</a> sign, and diminished <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Z56b78ebccefe6bf59439f506556ff19d\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Z56b78ebccefe6bf59439f506556ff19d\" data-section-id=\"FAXgl00\" data-sememe-id=\"bqaHCl\">proprioception</a>. The patient exhibits <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BR0z6f&anker=Ze881aa222001a5b126505000833daafb\" data-learningcard-id=\"BR0z6f\" data-anker=\"Ze881aa222001a5b126505000833daafb\" data-sememe-id=\"Nl0-CT\">cerebellar dysfunction</a> signs, such as wide-based gait and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BR0z6f&anker=Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-learningcard-id=\"BR0z6f\" data-anker=\"Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-section-id=\"J8asnm\" data-sememe-id=\"zf0rK2\">dysmetria</a>, without sensory deficits, which argues against <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=G60BmS&anker=Z3bdd63076128f8729c578ddd9af9bf86\" data-learningcard-id=\"G60BmS\" data-anker=\"Z3bdd63076128f8729c578ddd9af9bf86\" data-section-id=\"SucyqV0\" data-sememe-id=\"-hXDgB\">dorsal column</a> involvement.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=b70H4h&anker=Zf2fb6ce12d82eaa3f2ea7f2f0faa873a\" data-learningcard-id=\"b70H4h\" data-anker=\"Zf2fb6ce12d82eaa3f2ea7f2f0faa873a\" data-section-id=\"G71BMR0\" data-sememe-id=\"7sY4wq\">substantia nigra</a> pars reticulata is part of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WK0P2S&anker=Z2eb2f30c001f2b5fa17eeba767aa7b39\" data-learningcard-id=\"WK0P2S\" data-anker=\"Z2eb2f30c001f2b5fa17eeba767aa7b39\" data-section-id=\"dqcoxW0\" data-sememe-id=\"Jf0sM2\">basal ganglia</a>, influencing motor control by sending inhibitory signals to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-60DnS&anker=Zd64bfb19d2d1ca43c42b4d2c203deb2f\" data-learningcard-id=\"-60DnS\" data-anker=\"Zd64bfb19d2d1ca43c42b4d2c203deb2f\" data-section-id=\"Fvcgbe0\" data-sememe-id=\"ScXybC\">thalamus</a>. Lesions here typically cause parkinsonian features like <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=C30qkf&anker=Ze028c224550b58e35f3c56c431219172\" data-learningcard-id=\"C30qkf\" data-anker=\"Ze028c224550b58e35f3c56c431219172\" data-section-id=\"CnaqvO\" data-sememe-id=\"E_08Ji\">bradykinesia</a>, rigidity, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x30Ekf&anker=Zd8a43f20e2236f8f7138d0324b00bc7c\" data-learningcard-id=\"x30Ekf\" data-anker=\"Zd8a43f20e2236f8f7138d0324b00bc7c\" data-section-id=\"5Pci2c0\" data-sememe-id=\"SJaytl\">resting tremor</a>, not the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BR0z6f&anker=Z0600480d533e3f41ce2e6e77415aa54e\" data-learningcard-id=\"BR0z6f\" data-anker=\"Z0600480d533e3f41ce2e6e77415aa54e\" data-section-id=\"J8asnm\" data-sememe-id=\"DKc1iW0\">cerebellar signs</a> of wide-based gait, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BR0z6f&anker=Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-learningcard-id=\"BR0z6f\" data-anker=\"Zff75a2c72266aedf8c0ed865e181b5a7\" data-section-id=\"J8asnm\" data-sememe-id=\"zf0rK2\">dysmetria</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o500Og&anker=Z9ee37d95703755df723f2aede018c2ac\" data-learningcard-id=\"o500Og\" data-anker=\"Z9ee37d95703755df723f2aede018c2ac\" data-section-id=\"DAX1N00\" data-sememe-id=\"_f05K2\">dysdiadochokinesia</a> seen in this patient.</div>",
